Justice Minister Michael Masutha says the country is still battling with issues of inclusion. JOHANNESBURG Justice Minister Michael Masutha says more needs to be done to ensure the country s supreme laws include everyone who lives in South Africa. This year marks 20 years since the signing into law of the Constitution by late former President Nelson Mandela in Sharpeville.President Jacob Zuma is expected to address the commemoration on Saturday, under the theme 'Celebrating 20 years of the Constitution, Transforming Society and Uniting the Nation'.The Justice Minister says the country is still battling with issues of inclusion. We re a country in transition. We ve inherited an unenviable past of huge disparities economically and we re still battling inclusion. We still have a long way to finding the right balance. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)